column5: caught this little green guy in my bathroom this morning, figure it is some kind of tree frog has little stickys on its paws, also found two grayish ones in my ranger hiding under the lids in one of the channels.
EASTERN GRAY TREE FROG I THINK.
have you heard them 'sing' yet?  Loud is an understatement.
Living where i do..... i know frogs:whistling:
The others got it right, Eastern Gray
Did ya lick it to see if you could catch a buzz?    :tease:
I don't care how much evidence you think you may have, I am gonna call it a pickerel.
thanks guys your crackin me up
Try kissin it---maybe it'll turn into Danica Patrick
